<Link id="l00939" /><CodeLine lineNumber="939"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SwitchToNewBasicBlock - This method is used to jump to a new basic block.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00940" /><CodeLine lineNumber="940"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This function handles the actual updating of block and instruction iterators</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00941" /><CodeLine lineNumber="941"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// as well as execution of all of the PHI nodes in the destination block.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00942" /><CodeLine lineNumber="942"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="943"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This method does this because all of the PHI nodes must be executed</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00944" /><CodeLine lineNumber="944"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// atomically, reading their inputs before any of the results are updated.  Not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="945"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// doing this can cause problems if the PHI nodes depend on other PHI nodes for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="946"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// their inputs.  If the input PHI node is updated before it is read, incorrect</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="947"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// results can happen.  Thus we use a two phase approach.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="948"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
